The paper addresses the problem of predicting trajectories of vulnerable road users in complex urban environments, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) research. The proposed model uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) and reinforcement learning (RL), which are popular machine learning techniques in computer science (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the model is environmentally aware and able to classify the safety of trajectories, which suggests a potential application in systems and control (cs.SY).
